ive Gee","altText":"A Santander branch","height":"276","credit":"Clive Gee/PA","caption":"Photograph: Clive Gee/PA","width":"460"}}]},{"id":"gu-image-390369141","relation":"body","type":"image","assets":[{"type":"image","mimeType":"image/jpeg","file":"http://static.guim.co.uk/sys-images/Business/Pix/pictures/2012/5/18/1337360192073/President-of-the-European-008.jpg","typeData":{"source":"Reuters","photographer":"Yorgos Karahalis","altText":"President of the European Parliament Martin Schulz delivers a speech in Athens","height":"276","credit":"Yorgos Karahalis/Reuters","caption":"Photograph: Yorgos Karahalis/Reuters","width":"460"}}]},{"id":"gu-image-390369142","relation":"body","type":"image","assets":[{"type":"image","mimeType":"image/jpeg","file":"http://static.guim.co.uk/sys-images/Guardian/Pix/pictures/2012/3/20/1332272963426/Canadian-PM-Stephen-Harpe-007.jpg","typeData":{"source":"REUTERS","photographer":"Christinne Muschi","altText":"Canadian PM Stephen Harper","height":"276","credit":"Christinne Muschi/REUTERS","caption":"Canadian prime minister Stephen Harper. Photograph: Christinne Muschi/REUTERS","width":"460"}}]},{"id":"gu-image-390369143","relation":"body","type":"image","assets":[{"type":"image","mimeType":"image/jpeg","file":"http://static.guim.co.uk/sys-images/Business/Pix/pictures/2012/5/18/1337333355863/De-Standaard-interview-wi-001.jpg","typeData":{"source":"De Standaard ","altText":"De Standaard interview with Karel De Gucht, May 18th.","height":"200","credit":"De Standaard ","caption":"\"The Greek endgame has started\". Photograph: De Standaard ","width":"460"}}]},{"id":"gu-image-390369144","relation":"body","type":"image","assets":[{"type":"image","mimeType":"image/jpeg","file":"http://static.guim.co.uk/sys-images/Business/Pix/pictures/2012/5/18/1337330570545/FTSEs-biggest-fallers-18--001.jpg","typeData":{"source":"Reuters","altText":"FTSE's biggest fallers, 18 May.","height":"240","credit":"Reuters","caption":"The biggest fallers on the FTSE 1